{
  "title": "ionic login",
  "body": [
    "div",
    null,
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Authenticate with Ionic and retrieve a user token, which is stored in the CLI config. The most secure way to log in is running ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic login"
      ],
      " without arguments, which will prompt you for your credentials."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "If the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "IONIC_TOKEN"
      ],
      " environment variable is set, the CLI will automatically authenticate you. To retrieve your user token, first use ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic login"
      ],
      ", then print the token by running the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic config get -g tokens.user"
      ],
      " command."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic login"
      ],
      " will also accept ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "password"
      ],
      " through stdin, e.g.: ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "echo \"<password>\" | ionic login <email>"
      ],
      "."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "If you need to create an Ionic account, use ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic signup"
      ],
      "."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "You can reset your password in the ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://dashboard.ionicframework.com/reset-password"
        },
        "Dashboard"
      ],
      "."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "If you are having issues logging in, please get in touch with our ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://ion.link/support-request"
        },
        "Support"
      ],
      "."
    ]
  ],
